A common error I've seen in questjs is where an &quot;if&quot; has no [i:fnskk70h]condition[/i:fnskk70h].

e.g.

[code:fnskk70h]
if () {
    // some code here
}
[/code:fnskk70h]

So... don't do that. I think it happens when people add an &quot;if&quot; in the editor and then forget to do anything with it.
